  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Lamentations 4:10-11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Lamentations 4:10-11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The hands of the pitiful women have sodden their own children — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The affection of a mother toward her children is the strongest of all natural affections, and yet the famine hath forced that tender sex to divest themselves of it, and to boil and eat their own children. Thus was the prophecy of Moses, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:57",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", most awfully fulfilled; where see the notes, and on chap. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 2:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Lord hath accomplished his fury, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — God’s anger hath effected an entire destruction, so as not to leave one stone upon another.",
        "children": []
