  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Still more horrible was the misery of the women. In order to keep themselves from dying of hunger, mothers boiled their children for food to themselves; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 2:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". By the predicate \"compassionate,\" applied to hands, the contrast between this conduct and the nature, or the innate love, of mothers to their children, is made particularly prominent. בּרות is a noun  equals  בּרוּת, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 69:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On \"the destruction of the daughter of my people,\" cf. ",
        "children": []
